The infrastructure side of this can genuinely cost close to $0 while you're pre-revenue. The one thing that can't be fully free is the AI processing (Whisper + GPT-4o-mini calls) — but that's usage-based and tiny, so the fix there is capping it, not finding a free version of it. Here's the concrete mapping onto your existing stack:

The free-tier stack
Piece	Free option	Notes
Frontend (Next.js)	Vercel free tier	Built for Next.js, zero config, generous free limits
API (FastAPI)	Render free web service	Sleeps after inactivity, cold-starts on first request — fine pre-launch, annoying once you have real users
Database	Neon free tier	Serverless Postgres, scales to zero, works as a drop-in for your DATABASE_URL
Audio storage	Cloudinary free tier	Your storage_service.py already has a Cloudinary provider built in — just set STORAGE_PROVIDER=cloudinary and fill in the env vars
Email (password reset, etc.)	Resend or SendGrid free tier	100/day (SendGrid) is plenty at zero-to-small user counts
Error tracking	Sentry free developer tier	Add this now, costs nothing, saves you real pain later
